  "endpoint_derivation": "stateful",
  "_endpoint_derivation_note": "How per-resource REST endpoints are DERIVED (in addition to the architecture-mandated specials in `endpoints` above). 'stateful' = REST for every resource that has a state machine (lifecycle entities you operate on); the spec's value-object resources get no endpoints. 'all' = REST for every authored resource (the current spec has 57, so 'all' demands ~140 endpoints and reports most as gaps). A resource's REST surface is REQUIRED, so deleting it opens a gap — that is what stops the loop from deleting legitimate endpoints like /cases.",

